threads.title: 820-2915 no CPU vcore
threads.message:
Hi
I having a 820-2915 board, no liquid spilled. all power rails present but the CPU VCORE.

checked on u7400,pin 40,24,15 are all 5v
pin 2 TON=11-12V  pin1 EN=3.3V

replaced u7400, but no luck,still the same,any seen this before or any thoughts?

thanks

threads.title: 820-2915 no CPU vcore
threads.message: not much info got from customer, he said it had been like that when his cousin gave it to him. don't see liquid spilled and from the outside case of machine, doesn't look like it had been dropped hard

threads.title: 820-2915 no CPU vcore
threads.message: Can be absolutely anything. CPU needs to talk to U7400 to enable it. Anything can cause this, knocked off resistor, trace, etc.

threads.message: damn really don't know where to start now
